ROGUE - AKAI EDITION
====================

An ASCII dungeon crawler built with TypeScript + HTML5 Canvas.
Inspired by the original Rogue (1980). Run in any modern browser.


FEATURES
--------

  Procedural Dungeons
    - New map generated every run and every floor descent
    - BSP-style room placement with L-shaped corridor connections
    - Rooms vary in size and count, scaling with depth

  Field of View
    - Recursive shadowcasting FOV (radius 9)
    - Tiles outside your sight are dark; previously explored tiles
      remain visible in a dimmed "memory" state
    - Monsters are only drawn when in your line of sight

  Turn-Based Combat
    - Bump into a monster to attack
    - Damage rolls: random(1..attack) - defense, minimum 1
    - Monsters move and attack on every player turn

  Monsters (5 types, scale with depth)
    r  Rat      - weak, found on all floors
    g  Goblin   - standard early enemy
    o  Orc      - tougher, appears depth 2+
    T  Troll    - dangerous, appears depth 3+
    D  Dragon   - boss-tier, depth 5+

  Items (pick up with G)
    !  Health Potion    - restores 10-20 HP
    /  Lightning Scroll - zaps nearest monster for 15-25 damage
    )  Sword            - permanent +3 attack
    [  Shield           - permanent +2 defense

  Progression
    - 7 dungeon depths total
    - XP gained from kills; level ups grant +5 max HP and +1 attack
    - Reach the bottom of floor 7 and descend to win

  HUD
    - HP bar with color (green / yellow / red)
    - Attack, defense, level, XP, depth, turn counter displayed live
    - Message log shows last 6 combat and event messages


CONTROLS
--------

  Move          WASD  |  Arrow Keys  |  Numpad 8 4 6 2
  Diagonal      Y U B N  (top-left, top-right, bot-left, bot-right)
                Numpad 7 9 1 3
  Vim keys      H J K L  (left down up right)
  Wait a turn   .  or  Numpad 5
  Pick up item  G
  Descend       >  (must be standing on > stairs tile)
  Restart       R  (after death or victory)


HOW TO RUN
----------

  npm install
  npm run dev

  Then open http://localhost:5173 in your browser.

  Production build:
  npm run build


PROJECT LAYOUT
--------------

  src/
    types.ts      - shared interfaces and value enums (Tile, EntityType, ItemKind)
    dungeon.ts    - procedural map generation
    fov.ts        - recursive shadowcasting
    entities.ts   - player/monster/item factory functions and spawn logic
    combat.ts     - attack rolls, item use, monster pathfinding AI
    renderer.ts   - canvas ASCII renderer, HUD, start menu, game over screen
    game.ts       - game loop, state management, input handling
    main.ts       - entry point


TECH STACK
----------

  TypeScript 5, Vite 8, HTML5 Canvas API
  No runtime dependencies


GITHUB
